{
  "doc_id": "7021",
  "text": "In this study, we investigated the efficacy in vitro of a nano-complex of gold nanoparticles coated with indolicidin (AuNPs-indolicidin) in both preventing cell adhesion and eradicating the developed biofilms of some Candida clinical isolates and American Type Culture Collection (ATCC) strains. Furthermore, we investigated the expression levels of four biofilm-associated genes, namely EFG1, HWP1, ALS1, and ALS3. [CITATION_1] The activity of efflux pumps is widely described as the main cause of drug resistance in C. albicans, with an overexpression of CDR1 and CDR2 genes even after short exposure to antifungal drugs. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Therefore, this study also investigated the possible involvement of efflux pumps and the expression of the connected CDR1 and CDR2 genes after the treatment of Candida biofilms.",
